trans-unit.source: Implements an event provider that maps ASP.NET health-monitoring events to Windows Management Instrumentation (WMI) events.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Management.WmiWebEventProvider"></xref> class.
This constructor is used internally by the ASP.NET health-monitoring system.

You will never use it to create an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Management.TraceWebEventProvider> class, but you can call this constructor when you implement your own provider type that inherits from this class.
Removes all events from the provider's buffer.
When this method is called, all the events in the provider's buffer are immediately removed, regardless of how much time has elapsed since the last write or how many events are in the buffer.
The time of the last write is reset to the time of the flushing action.
Calling this method when the buffering mechanism is not enabled has no effect.
Sets the initial values for this object.
ASP.NET calls the Initialize method after calling the <xref:System.Web.Management.WmiWebEventProvider.%23ctor%2A> constructor.
This method is called to initialize the <xref:System.Web.Management.WmiWebEventProvider> class with the configuration settings and name specified in the configuration file.
The name used in the configuration file to identify this provider.
A <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection"></xref> object that specifies the attributes assigned for this provider in the configuration file.
Processes the event passed to the provider.
This is the method that ASP.NET health monitoring calls to start the processing of the event.
The <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent"></xref> object to process.
The event could not be raised.
Performs tasks associated with shutting down the provider.
ASP.NET calls the <xref:System.Web.Management.EventLogWebEventProvider.Shutdown%2A> method when the application domain that hosts the Web application terminates.
The method is called to perform tasks that will allow the application to end gracefully.
